# Document 02 — TRD

Locks technical decisions so the agent stays coherent across every file.

## Required sections

- Frontend framework and version
- Backend runtime / API layer
- Database type and provider
- Authentication method
- Hosting and deployment targets
- Third-party APIs (name, purpose, tier)
- Key libraries
- Environment variable names (not secrets)
- Hard constraints (mobile-first, free tier only, etc.)

## Agent rules

- Use only the stack declared in the TRD. Do not swap frameworks mid-project without explicit approval.
- Match folder structure and naming conventions from the TRD.
- List every new env var in the TRD when adding integrations.
